{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring to the boil then reduce heat and simmer until cooked. Meanwhile, continue with recipe.","Place Parmesan cheese in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place chickpeas and parsley in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula.","Once potatoes are cooked, drain then run under cold water to cool.","Add cooked potatoes, reserved grated cheese, egg, salt, pepper, 50 g flour and ham then mix <nobr>8 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Shape mixture into 20 balls (approx. Ø 3 cm) then coat in remaining 20 g flour.","Heat oil in a frying pan over a medium heat and fry balls for 10 minutes until golden brown, turning occassionally, then drain on paper towel.","Serve hot or cold with chopped vegetables."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g floury potatoes, peeled, cut in pieces (4 cm)","50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","200 g cooked chickpeas, rinsed and drained","2 - 3 sprigs fresh parsley, leaves only","1 large egg","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 pinch ground pepper","70 g 00 flour (pasta flour)","100 g dry-cured ham, diced","extra virgin olive oil, for frying","120 g carrots, cut in sticks","120 g red peppers, cut in sticks","120 g cucumber, cut in sticks"]}],"id":"r124141","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-Nq3ZuE9baUo\/XZMulpKoeCI\/AAAAAAAAaHI\/4skJ3kUK-oo4yDe6HthtFWTwn0YHHpxmwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_M6-1xcQ28frqur-G.png","title":"Chickpea and Ham Balls","publishedAt":"2016-07-04T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.8 g","fat":"2.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"6 g","calories":"255 kJ \/ 61 kcal"},"usefulItems":"saucepan, frying pan, paper towel, hob","basicInfo":["easy","25m","35m","20 pieces"]}